            "description": "Valaris Limited (NYSE: VAL) recently announced a significant 1,064-day contract extension with Petrobras (NYSE: PBR) for the drillship VALARIS DS-4. This extension is set to begin in November 2027 and is anticipated to contribute around $447 million to Valaris' contract backlog. Additionally, the company has made adjustments to the day rate for the existing contract, resulting in a decrease of approximately $21 million in the backlog from April 2026 onwards. Despite this positive news, Valaris stock is currently experiencing a decline in value, prompting speculation on the reasons behind this situation.",
